  {
    "title": "Great rhino sightings",
    "rating": 4,
    "travelDate": "2022-04",
    "publishedDate": "2022-05-30",
    "text": "After a mix-up in our 3-night reservation for a 2-bedroomed cottage (caused by our Botswana travel agent not by the Park officials) we were accommodated in a chalet normally used by teachers at a facility for wildlife education. This accommodation was very basic but we were most grateful as the park was overflowing with visitors.\n\nAbsolutely wonderful sightings of various animals and birds, including 26 white and 1 black rhino on our last afternoon! We were surprised at the size of the park, and it was reassuring to note the presence of many armed army personnel within and on the borders of the reserve protecting its assets.\n\nDefinitely a place to be revisited!",
