  {
    "title": "Great game experience, average accommodation.",
    "rating": 3,
    "travelDate": "2021-05",
    "publishedDate": "2021-05-30",
    "text": "We stayed at the Rhino Sanctuary for two nights en route to Kubu Island.  There is a lot of game in this reserve - well worth driving around, especially to the various pans.  We really enjoyed this aspect of the reserve.  \n\nThe accommodation in the chalets is extremely basic, it consists of beds, a small bathroom and a table.  The upper part of the walls on the A frame is made of netting, so one is unable to \"close\" this area up.  This resulted in all of us being absolutely freezing during the night.\n\nWe ate at the restaurant and found the food to be satisfactory, although somewhat excessively priced.  The service was also very slow due to what seemed like minimal staff.  We assumed this was as a result of Covid.",
    "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g479197-d2296308-r790429947-Khama_Rhino_Sanctuary-Serowe_Central_District.html",
